'''Nomad-Damon''' was a traveler who introduced many [[Ubese Thorn-Back War Dragon]]s to populated worlds during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]].<ref name="Design An Alien">{{GalaxyCite|7|Design An Alien}}</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
Nomad-Damon was created by [[Mark Rehkopf]], a ''[[Star Wars]]'' fan, for the backstory of his [[Ubese Thorn-Back War Dragon]] entry in the ''[[Design An Alien]]'' contest held for ''[[Star Wars Galaxy Magazine]]'', which was eventually published in the [[Star Wars Galaxy Magazine 7|seventh issue]] of the magazine in [[1996]]. [[Leland Chee]], the [[Lucasfilm]] continuity editor, later stated that the "Design an Alien" material was [[canon]].<ref name="tt">{{SWBoards|url=thread.jspa?threadID=152583&start=690#14724917|thread=Holocron continuity database questions|user=[[Leland Chee|Leland Y Chee]]|date=2006-05-03|time=5:45 PM|quote=Star Wars Galaxy Magazine #7 published the winners of the "Design an Alien" contest, where fans were encouraged to submit artwork and backstories of new SW aliens. Are these aliens canon? [...] Yes, though any text discrepencies with other sources would likely to superceded by the other source.}}</ref>

